package etzhayyim:aburi;

// The aburi 炙り actor's executable interface — personal-tracking-exposure analysis as a WASI
// Component-Model component built with componentize-py (ADR-2606161630 + ADR-2606014600).
//
// The result is an exposure READOUT (who-tracks-you / leakiest-platform / data-spread /
// reciprocity-gap) over the member's OWN graph. It carries own_data=true + reciprocity_restoring
// =true and is structurally non-adjudicating (G3): naming a collector is a DISCLOSED catalogue
// fact, never a verdict. The WASM sandbox has no network and no ambient FS, so the component
// cannot exfiltrate, phone home, or build a dossier — the host owns the log (G7/no-server-key).

world aburi-actor {
  /// Run the exposure analyzer over the embedded representative seed (or host-supplied graph).
  /// Returns JSON: { who_tracks_you:[...], surface_leak:[...], data_spread:[...],
  ///                 reciprocity_gap:[...], own_data:true, reciprocity_restoring:true }.
  export analyze: func() -> string;

  /// Emit the kotoba Datom log (EAVT) for the exposure graph as EDN text.
  /// Ground datoms are op :add; derived readouts are flagged transient (N1/G2). The emit attr
  /// allowlist carries no credential / raw-identifier attr, so none can be projected (G8).
  export datoms: func(tx: u32) -> string;

  /// Honest coverage report (markdown): surface/permission/collector/catalogue/datatype + gap map (G5).
  export coverage: func() -> string;
}
